But I had the same idea of heating water with it for a turbine, but I also wanted to add a Fresnel Lense on top to also heat the water,  the water would have to be running through a small sphere or maybe just a straight pipe, and to avoid using an electrical pump, there has to be a way to use convection to naturally move the water if needed. It could be like a big pet water feeder . It goes to the small sphere tank being quickly heated by the parabolic mirror and lense on top, the steam has to go somewhere, so have it spin a turbine and rain back into the feeder. 
I think it can totally work, and maybe the lens isn't even needed, but I've always wanted to try it. I might make it a goal

